=== Etymology ===
#'''Candidate''' comes from Latin ''candidatus'' meaning "a person who is standing for public office", which in turn comes from ''candidus'' meaning "candid" or "white", in reference to Roman candidates wearing bleached white togas as a symbol of purity at a public forum.

== [[noun]] ==
#a person who is running in an election or who is applying to a position for a job.

